The paper discusses a practical approach to verifying C/C++ programs that use mathematical libraries, which falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of abstract interpretation, symbolic model checking, and constraint-based test data generation, which are techniques commonly used in programming languages (cs.PL), logic (cs.LO), formal methods (cs.FL), and embedded systems (cs.ET) sub-categories.
